{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/getAllowlistForFeature","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy\"><code>FeaturePolicy</code></a></strong></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>getAllowlistForFeature()</code></strong>\n  method of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy\"><code>FeaturePolicy</code></a> allows query of the allow list for a\n  specific feature for the current Feature Policy.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">const allowlist = FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature(feature)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameter","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<h4 id=\"feature_name\">Feature name</h4>\n<p>A specific feature name must be specified.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  An <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Feature_Policy/Using_Feature_Policy\">Allow list</a> for the\n  specified feature.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"errors","title":"Errors","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The function will raise a warning if the specified Feature Policy directive name is not\n  known. However, it will also return empty array, indicating that no origin is allowed to\n  use the feature.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example","title":"Example","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The following example prints all the origins that are allowed to use Camera API by the\n  Feature Policy. Please note that Camera API might be restricted by the Permissions API,\n  if the user did not grant the corresponding permission yet.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// First, get the Feature Policy object</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> featurePolicy <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>featurePolicy\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Then query feature for specific</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> allowlist <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> featurePolicy<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getAllowlistForFeature</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"camera\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> origin <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> allowlist<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>origin<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[],"query":"api.FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/getAllowlistForFeature/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Errors","id":"errors"},{"text":"Example","id":"example"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The getAllowlistForFeature()\n  method of the FeaturePolicy allows query of the allow list for a\n  specific feature for the current Feature Policy.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:27:14.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature()","locale":"fr","native":"Fran√ßais"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/featurepolicy/getallowlistforfeature","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/featurepolicy/getallowlistforfeature/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/4e233c16c6f0d347972c5c762f5b836318a46124","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy","title":"FeaturePolicy"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/getAllowlistForFeature","title":"FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature()"}],"pageTitle":"FeaturePolicy.getAllowlistForFeature() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}